    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**4 new files to create, 1 existing file to modify:**\n\n### New Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` | Core implementation |\n| `packages/next/geo.js` | Public CJS entry point (mirrors `server.js`) |\n| `packages/next/geo.d.ts` | Type re-exports (mirrors `server.d.ts`) |\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` | Jest test suite |\n\n### Core Implementation (`geo.ts`)\n- **`Geo` interface** — 7 optional string fields: `city`, `country`, `countryCode`, `region`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `timezone`\n- **`COUNTRY_NAMES` map** — 10 entries (AU, BR, CA, CN, DE, FR, GB, IN, JP, US)\n- **`geoFromHeaders(headers)`** — reads Vercel headers + Cloudflare `cf-ipcountry` fallback; `null → undefined` via `?? undefined`; derives `country` from `countryCode`\n- **`geo({ headers })`** — thin wrapper, mirrors `userAgent()` signature exactly\n- **`isInRegion(geo, regions)`** — case-insensitive `countryCode` membership check\n- **`geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2)`** — Haversine formula returning km\n\n### Existing File Modified\n- **`packages/next/package.json`** — add `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` to `files` array after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical g-after-f)\n\n### Tests (10 cases)\nCovers: all Vercel headers, missing headers, country name lookup, unknown country code, Cloudflare fallback, Vercel-over-Cloudflare precedence, case-insensitive region matching, NY→London ~5570 km (±50 km tolerance), zero distance for identical points.\n\n### Verification\n1. `pnpm --filter=next types` — fast type check\n2. `pnpm test-unit -- --testPathPattern=geo.test` — unit tests\n3. `pnpm --filter=next build` — confirms dist output emitted",
